rComments: Professor Sarris truly cares about making his students passionate about fields and waves, and it shows with the way he delivers his lectures. Although I found the subject boring, he was a great professor in terms of teaching it and making the experience as easy as possible!
Really wants his students to do well and is willing to sit down and explain the material again.. Lectures do get boring at times though.

Great professor that made ECE320 much more interesting and entertaining. He doesn't use notes during his lectures- he just knows his material that well. Like others have mentioned, he genuinely wants his students to succeed, and he's available for office hours to help clarify concepts. He can seem intimidating at first, but he's surprisingly funny.
Fantastic lectures. Uses no notes, all by heart.

Very good lecturer and always willing to help although he is perhaps a bit too focused on the theory (he did basically no examples during lecture).  His jokes can be pretty funny, which is good because you might need something to keep you awake during the more boring lectures in this class.
Best prof for circuit theory...but speaks bit fast and says all the important concepts in jus one breath....over all guy is interted in teaching and is GOOD.

Overall a very good prof. He is extremely helpful and sincerely wants you to succeed. Occasionally will confuse you when he decides to do a proof or something on the board and has high expectations in terms of test performance.
****.. No idea what so ever of what he is doing..
